
[1]rock-crystal

   ROCK-CRYS'TAL, n. The most perfect variety of silicious earth or
   quartz; limpid quartz. When purest it is white or colorless, but it is
   found of a grayish or yellowish white, pale yellow or citron. Its most
   usual form is that of hexagonal prisms, surmounted by hexagonal
   pyramids.
